Author: Reissland
How was Infant Alertness Measured: Eyes open, hands resting or waving without obstructing face (nonmodeling session); eyes open and looking at the experimenter and hands resting or waving without obstructing face (modeling session). Also eyeblinks
Measure of Alertness or Attention by Inf: Mean number of blinks per minute was 10.7 when broad mouth, 9.3 when pursed mouth, 6.5 in nonmodeling condition

Author: Soussignan
How was Infant Alertness Measured: Visual attention of at least 6 s toward the stimulus
Reason for Dropouts: 12 for fussiness, sleepiness or hiccuping and 15 for visual attention of less than 6 s toward the stimulus
